\Slot\

==Noun==
[[Cf.]]: [[close]], [[sluice]]

1. A broad, flat, wooden bar; a slat or sloat.

2. A bolt or bar for fastening a door. ([[Prov. Eng.]]).

3. A narrow depression, perforation, or aperture; esp., one for the reception of a piece fitting or sliding in it.

4. The track of a deer; hence, a track of any kind. --[[w:Milton]].

      As a bloodhound follows the slot of a hurt deer. --[[w:Sir W. Scott]].

==Verb==

===Transitive===
See slot a bar.

To shut with violence; to slam; as, to slot a door. ([[Obs.]] or
[[Prov. Eng.]]]).